.TH man_1_simple_shell

.Sh NAME
.B Simple Shell
Our command language interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B
$ [command_file[argument...]]


.SH DESCRIPTION
.B
The Simple Shell utility is a command language interpreter that shall execute commands read from  a command line string, the standard input, ot a specified file.

.SH OPERANDS

.SH ENVIORMENT VARIABLES
.B ENV
.P This variable, when and only when an interacive shell is invoked, shall be subjectred to expansion by the shell, and the resulting value shall be used as a pathname of a file containing shell commands to execute in the current environment.

.B PATH
.P This varibale shall represent the sequence of path prefixes at the time of login 
